ACT:
 Civil Service-Orissa-Age of superannuation raised from 55 to 58 years by Government resolution dated May 21, 1963- Liberalised Pension Rules did not have effect that employee should have put in 30 years service before he could be retired at 55-Guidlines to Heads of the Departments mentioning inter alia that an officer lacking integrity may be retired at 55 This did not cast stigma on every officer who was retired at 55-Article 311(2) of Constitution not attracted.
 
